      <abstract>
        <p>Clearly Tech, new company, will manufacture scented candles in converted factory in Saugerties, NY (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A new company that will make scented candles and other wick and wax illuminations is investing $6.75 million to convert a vacant factory in Saugerties, N.Y., into its headquarters and production site.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>A new company that will make scented candles and other wick and wax illuminations is investing $6.75 million to convert a vacant factory in Saugerties, N.Y., into its headquarters and production site.</p>
        <p>The company, Clearly Tech, will receive $500,000 in state aid to offset  its costs in setting up shop in the Ulster County community, where, state officials say, it will be operating with 200 employees by the end of the year.</p>
        <p>The Empire State Development Corporation said yesterday that the company hoped to have more than 500 workers in five years.</p>
        <p>Joseph P. Fried</p>
      </block>
